"Yunnan: Coordinating and Regulating the Management of Rural Public Benefit Posts - Xinhua News" 
"In order to continuously help and support the employment of people who have been lifted out of poverty, and to consolidate and expand the achievements of poverty alleviation, Yunnan Province recently issued policies to promote the management of rural public benefit posts in rural revitalization, in order to fully advance rural revitalization. New China News Agency, Kunming, December 12th (Reporter Lin Bifeng)" 
"According to the relevant responsible person from the Yunnan Province Department of Human Resources and Social Security, at present, Yunnan has developed 448,300 rural public benefit posts, used for employment of difficult groups in rural areas such as those who have been lifted out of poverty, playing an important role in helping poverty-stricken people achieve employment and income increase, consolidating poverty alleviation achievements, and effectively improving various rural public services." 
"This new regulation was jointly issued by seven departments including Yunnan Department of Human Resources and Social Security, rural revitalization, finance, etc. It mainly unifies and regulates the scope of recruitment for rural public benefit posts at the grassroots level, financial management, post development, and post management." 
"In terms of post development and setup, the new regulation clearly specifies that it will be set according to the principles of "setting posts as needed, determining personnel based on posts, dynamic management, and total control," "whoever develops, whoever uses, whoever is responsible," and "one post per person, voluntary and open, and unified management."
"The recruitment process must be carried out in accordance with steps such as announcement, declaration, review, publicity, employment, pre-job training and arrangement." 
"In addition, the new regulations have also clearly defined the specific responsibilities of the main development department for rural public welfare posts, the subsidy standards and methods for rural public welfare posts, stipulated that the development departments of each rural public welfare post should purchase accidental injury commercial insurance for the personnel stationed in the rural public welfare post; and required relevant departments to regularly supervise the distribution of subsidies for rural public welfare posts."